15/06/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Minister of the Interior, Public Administration and Decentralisation Constantine Skandalidis presented the new draft law on the public sector Friday (13 June). The bill aims to simplify administrative procedures, guarantee better service, and introduce new rules to evaluate the work of state institutions and public administration employees. The cabinet will first discuss the draft with the Civil Servants' Union and then table it for parliamentary approval. (MPA - 13/06/03)
